The paper discusses query processing on large graphs, which is a topic that falls under several CS sub-categories. The use of partitioning and divide-and-conquer approaches suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DB (databases) or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The focus on scalability and response time trade-offs suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IR (information retrieval) or cs.SI (social and information networks). Finally, the use of quantitative metrics and heuristics suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing).
